name: websocket
description:
Module Overview

This module provides an implementation for connecting and interacting with WebSocket endpoints. The module facilitates two types of network entry points as ‘Client’ and ‘Listener’.

WebSocket Module

This module also provides support for WebSockets. There are two types of WebSocket endpoints: WebSocketClient and WebSocketListener. Both endpoints support all WebSocket frames. The WebSocketClient has a callback service.

There are two types of services for WebSockets. The service of the server has the WebSocketCaller as the resource parameter and the callback service of the client has WebSocketClient as the resource parameter. The WebSocket services have a fixed set of resources that do not have a resource config. The incoming messages are passed to these resources.

WebSocket upgrade: During a WebSocket upgrade, the initial message received is an HTTP request. To intercept this request and perform the upgrade explicitly with custom headers, the user must create an HTTP resource with WebSocket-specific configurations as follows:

@http:ResourceConfig {
    webSocketUpgrade: {
        upgradePath: "/{name}",
        upgradeService: chatApp
    }
}
resource function upgrader(http:Caller caller, http:Request req, string name) {
}

The upgradeService is a server callback service.

onOpen resource: As soon as the WebSocket handshake is completed and the connection is established, the onOpen resource is dispatched. This resource is only available in the service of the server.

onText resource: The received text messages are dispatched to this resource.

onBinary resource: The received binary messages are dispatched to this resource.

onPing and onPong resources: The received ping and pong messages are dispatched to these resources respectively.

onIdleTimeout: This resource is dispatched when the idle timeout is reached. The idleTimeout has to be configured either in the WebSocket service or the client configuration.

onClose: This resource is dispatched when a close frame with a statusCode and a reason is received.

onError: This resource is dispatched when an error occurs in the WebSocket connection. This will always be preceded by a connection closure with an appropriate close frame.

For more information, see the following.

  • WebSocket Basic Example
  • HTTP to WebSocket Upgrade Example
  • WebSocket Chat Application
  • WebSocket Proxy Server
  • Client Endpoint
  • Retry
  • Failover
  • Cookie

fields.name: path
fields.description: Path of the WebSocket service

fields.name: subProtocols
fields.description: Negotiable sub protocol by the service

fields.name: idleTimeoutInSeconds
fields.description: Idle timeout for the client connection. Upon timeout, onIdleTimeout resource (if defined) in the server service will be triggered. Note that this overrides the timeoutInMillis config in the http:Listener.

fields.name: maxFrameSize
fields.description: The maximum payload size of a WebSocket frame in bytes. If this is not set or is negative or zero, the default frame size will be used.

fields.name: targetUrls
fields.description: The set of URLs, which are used to connect to the server

fields.name: failoverIntervalInMillis
fields.description: The maximum number of milliseconds to delay a failover attempt

fields.name: callbackService
fields.description: The callback service of the client. Resources in this service gets called on the receipt of messages from the server

fields.name: subProtocols
fields.description: Negotiable sub protocols of the client

fields.name: customHeaders
fields.description: Custom headers, which should be sent to the server

fields.name: idleTimeoutInSeconds
fields.description: Idle timeout of the client. Upon timeout, the onIdleTimeout resource (if defined) of the client service will be triggered

fields.name: readyOnConnect
fields.description: Set to true if the client is ready to receive messages as soon as the connection is established. This is set to true by default. If changed to false, the ready() function of the WebSocketClient needs to be called once to start receiving messages

fields.name: secureSocket
fields.description: SSL/TLS-related options

fields.name: maxFrameSize
fields.description: The maximum payload size of a WebSocket frame in bytes If this is not set, is negative, or is zero, the default frame size of 65536 will be used.

fields.name: webSocketCompressionEnabled
fields.description: Enable support for compression in the WebSocket

fields.name: handShakeTimeoutInSeconds
fields.description: Time (in seconds) that a connection waits to get the response of the webSocket handshake. If the timeout exceeds, then the connection is terminated with an error.If the value < 0, then the value sets to the default value(300).

fields.name: maxCount
fields.description: The maximum number of retry attempts. If the count is zero, the client will retry indefinitely

fields.name: intervalInMillis
fields.description: The number of milliseconds to delay before attempting to reconnect

fields.name: backOffFactor
fields.description: The rate of increase of the reconnect delay. Allows reconnect attempts to back off when problems persist

fields.name: maxWaitIntervalInMillis
fields.description: Maximum time of the retry interval in milliseconds

fields.name: host
fields.description: The remote host IP

fields.name: port
fields.description: The remote port

fields.name: host
fields.description: The host name/IP of the endpoint

fields.name: http1Settings
fields.description: Configurations related to HTTP/1.x protocol

fields.name: secureSocket
fields.description: The SSL configurations for the service endpoint. This needs to be configured in order to communicate through HTTPS.

fields.name: httpVersion
fields.description: Highest HTTP version supported by the endpoint resource, filters can applied

fields.name: timeoutInMillis
fields.description: Period of time in milliseconds that a connection waits for a read/write operation. Use value 0 to disable timeout

fields.name: server
fields.description: The server name which should appear as a response header

fields.name: webSocketCompressionEnabled
fields.description: Enable support for compression in WebSocket

records.name: ListenerConfiguration
records.description: Provides a set of configurations for HTTP service endpoints.

fields.name: keepAlive
fields.description: Can be set to either KEEPALIVE_AUTO, which respects the connection header, or KEEPALIVE_ALWAYS, which always keeps the connection alive, or KEEPALIVE_NEVER, which always closes the connection

fields.name: maxPipelinedRequests
fields.description: Defines the maximum number of requests that can be processed at a given time on a single connection. By default 10 requests can be pipelined on a single cinnection and user can change this limit appropriately.

fields.name: maxUriLength
fields.description: Maximum allowed length for a URI. Exceeding this limit will result in a 414 - URI Too Long response.

fields.name: maxHeaderSize
fields.description: Maximum allowed size for headers. Exceeding this limit will result in a 413 - Payload Too Large response.

fields.name: maxEntityBodySize
fields.description: Maximum allowed size for the entity body. By default it is set to -1 which means there is no restriction maxEntityBodySize, On the Exceeding this limit will result in a 413 - Payload Too Large response.

fields.name: trustStore
fields.description: Configures the trust store to be used

fields.name: keyStore
fields.description: Configures the key store to be used

fields.name: certFile
fields.description: A file containing the certificate of the server

fields.name: keyFile
fields.description: A file containing the private key of the server

fields.name: keyPassword
fields.description: Password of the private key if it is encrypted

fields.name: trustedCertFile
fields.description: A file containing a list of certificates or a single certificate that the server trusts

fields.name: protocol
fields.description: SSL/TLS protocol related options

fields.name: certValidation
fields.description: Certificate validation against CRL or OCSP related options

fields.name: ciphers
fields.description: List of ciphers to be used (e.g.: TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256, TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_128_CBC_SHA)

fields.name: sslVerifyClient
fields.description: The type of client certificate verification. (e.g.: "require" or "optional")

fields.name: shareSession
fields.description: Enable/disable new SSL session creation

fields.name: handshakeTimeoutInSeconds
fields.description: SSL handshake time out

fields.name: sessionTimeoutInSeconds
fields.description: SSL session time out

fields.name: ocspStapling
fields.description: Enable/disable OCSP stapling

listeners.name: Listener
listeners.description: This is used for creating Websocket server endpoints. An Websocket server endpoint is capable of responding to remote callers. The Listener is responsible for initializing the endpoint using the provided configurations.

constants.name: KEEPALIVE_AUTO
constants.description: Decides to keep the connection alive or not based on the connection header of the client request }

constants.name: KEEPALIVE_ALWAYS
constants.description: Keeps the connection alive irrespective of the connection header value }

constants.name: KEEPALIVE_NEVER
constants.description: Closes the connection irrespective of the connection header value }
